        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">According to Lv et al (2021), the installed capacity for propylene in 2019 in China was 3.79E10 kg. According to the same publication, 24% of propylene in China are produced from methanol. 

According to HSBC Global Research (2014), the expected coal-to-olefins projects in China are expected to show a ethylene-to-propylene ratio of 0.81.

The latter information was used to identify the production volume of the following activites available in the ecoinvent Database (since v3.10); 
1) light olefins production, from methanol-to-olefins conversion, ethylene-to-propylene ratio of 0.67
2) light olefins production, from methanol-to-olefins conversion, ethylene-to-propylene ratio of 1.51
3) propylene production, from methanol-to-propylene conversion

An average capacity factor of 83% was assumed.

Reference:
Lv, L.; Song, G.; Zhao, X.; Chen, J. (2021): Environmental Burdens of China’s Propylene manufacturing: Comparative life-cycle assessment and scenario analysis, Science of the Total Environment, 799, 149451.
HSBC Global Research (2014), Coal-to-chemicals, A potential growth engine but with environmental constraints, available at: https://www.longfinance.net/media/documents/hsbc_coal_to_chems_environment.pdf, assessed in 2023-10-09.
</productionVolumeComment>
